# Topic 2: Access Modifiers
# --------------------------------------------------

## 1. Definition
- Access Modifiers control **who can access** a class, field, or method.
- They set the **visibility/scope** of class members.
- Java has 4 access modifiers: `public`, `private`, `protected`, and `default` (no keyword).

---

## 2. Real-Life Example
- **public** тЖТ A park. Anyone from anywhere can enter.
- **private** тЖТ Your bedroom. Only you can access it.
- **protected** тЖТ A family home. Family members (subclasses) and people in the same area (package) can enter.
- **default** тЖТ A society/colony gate. Only people inside the colony (same package) can enter.

---

## 3. Why Do We Use It?
- To protect sensitive data from outside access.
- To control which parts of code are visible to other classes.
- Core part of **Encapsulation**.

---

## 4. Types

| Modifier | Same Class | Same Package | Subclass (other pkg) | Other Package |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| `public` | тЬЕ | тЬЕ | тЬЕ | тЬЕ |
| `protected` | тЬЕ | тЬЕ | тЬЕ | тЭМ |
| `default` | тЬЕ | тЬЕ | тЭМ | тЭМ |
| `private` | тЬЕ | тЭМ | тЭМ | тЭМ |

---

## 5. Key Rules
- `private` тЖТ most restricted. Only accessible within the same class.
- `public` тЖТ least restricted. Accessible from everywhere.
- `default` тЖТ no keyword written. Package-level access only.
- `protected` тЖТ like default + accessible in subclasses of other packages.
- Class itself can only be `public` or `default` (not private/protected).

---

## 6. Syntax

```java
public class MyClass {
    public int a;       // accessible everywhere
    private int b;      // accessible only inside MyClass
    protected int c;    // accessible in same package + subclasses
    int d;              // default - accessible only in same package
}
```

---

## 7. Complete Java Program

```java
// File: AccessModifiers.java

class BankAccount {                        // Class with different access modifiers

    public String accountHolder;           // public - anyone can access this
    private double balance;                // private - only this class can access
    protected String bankName;             // protected - same package + subclasses
    String accountType;                    // default - only same package

    public void setBalance(double amount) {  // public method to set private field
        if (amount >= 0) {                   // validation before setting
            balance = amount;                // setting the private field
        }
    }

    public double getBalance() {           // public method to read private field
        return balance;                    // returning private field value
    }

    public void displayInfo() {            // public method - accessible everywhere
        System.out.println("Holder: " + accountHolder);    // prints account holder
        System.out.println("Bank: " + bankName);           // prints bank name
        System.out.println("Type: " + accountType);        // prints account type
        System.out.println("Balance: " + balance);         // can access private here (same class)
    }
}

public class AccessModifiers {                       // Main class
    public static void main(String[] args) {

        BankAccount acc = new BankAccount();         // creating object

        acc.accountHolder = "Prikshit";              // OK - public field
        acc.bankName = "SBI";                        // OK - protected, same package
        acc.accountType = "Savings";                 // OK - default, same package
        // acc.balance = 5000;                       // ERROR - private, cannot access directly

        acc.setBalance(5000);                        // OK - using public method to set private field
        System.out.println(acc.getBalance());        // OK - using public method to read private field

        acc.displayInfo();                           // calling public method
    }
}
```

